                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On November 6 Ambassador Bruce and Alexandre Parodi, Secretary-General of the
                    French Ministry of Foreign Affairs, signed for their respective Governments an
                    agreement regarding the establishment and operation of a line of communication
                    across France, including annexes on the juridical status of U.S. Armed Forces
                    personnel stationed in France and in French North Africa, financing of the Line
                    of Communication, and radio facilities. There were also an exchange of letters
                    with regard to displaced persons of Polish origin to be employed by United
                    States Forces on the territory of Metropolitan France and a letter signed by
                    Ambassador Bruce with regard to the status of U.S. military personnel in French
                    North Africa. Documentation on these subjects is in Department of State file No.
                    711.56351.</p>
            </div>
